== Roasted Carrots & Mashed Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Peel and dice @Yukon gold potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil; cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with @sour cream{2%tablespoon} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Caramelized Onion ==

While potatoes cook, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add @sugar{1%teaspoon} and a splash of water; cook until caramelized, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Steak & Mushroom Sauce ==

Pat @sirloin steak{14%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Add @butter{1%tablespoon} and mushrooms to pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @beef demi-glace{1}; add ¼ cup water. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer.

Stir in @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice steak against the grain.

== To Serve ==

Divide mashed potatoes, carrots, and steak between plates. Top mashed potatoes with caramelized onion. Top steak with mushroom sauce and serve.